00:21:08.200 --> 00:21:10.730
&gt;&gt;Bill Wallauer: I am a foraging machine,
yeah.

00:21:10.730 --> 00:21:11.730
[laughter]

00:21:11.730 --> 00:21:15.270
And it's really interesting 'cause I've lived
in Gombe for all those years. And there's

00:21:15.270 --> 00:21:19.130
some season that the food's not very nice.
And it's interesting. The chimps don't get

00:21:19.130 --> 00:21:24.290
that excited about it. When they get really
excited it's over something super sweet. So,

00:21:24.290 --> 00:21:31.650
there's that, there's a real connection between
us liking sweet and salty foods as well.

00:21:31.650 --> 00:21:35.290
They're pretty rare. And those are the ones
in the forest I obviously like. It's the ones

00:21:35.290 --> 00:21:40.630
they like as well. Also, if you're high-ranking,
you get the top of the tree because that's

00:21:40.630 --> 00:21:46.720
where, if you think about this, in your own
backyard, if you have an apple tree, the juiciest,

00:21:46.720 --> 00:21:51.670
ripest fruit is gonna be the highest stuff
in the tree because it's getting all the sunlight.

00:21:51.670 --> 00:21:55.620
So, it's ripening better. And so, if you're
low-ranking, you're going to the lower parts

00:21:55.620 --> 00:22:00.170
of the tree eating the lower fruit. If you're
high-ranking, you can be right in the top.

00:22:00.170 --> 00:22:06.840
But yeah, Ilove chimp food. It's funny that
in certain times of year, I start craving.

00:22:06.840 --> 00:22:12.100
I think there's a real connection between
what we used to eat just for nutrition and

00:22:12.100 --> 00:22:15.830
also for like, for medicine.

00:22:15.830 --> 00:22:19.950
There's a real correlation between that, because
I really crave some of this food that I no

00:22:19.950 --> 00:22:25.800
longer get. There's something in arugula that's
really similar to what Jane called "chimp

00:22:25.800 --> 00:22:29.670
spinach" all these years ago that I eat at
the end of the day that chimps just stuff

00:22:29.670 --> 00:22:33.640
this stuff down at the end of the day. There's
some chemical in it that when arugula start

00:22:33.640 --> 00:22:36.820
getting popular, it's like, "Oh, yeah. I feel
like I'm at home now."

00:22:36.820 --> 00:22:37.820
[laughter]

00:22:37.820 --> 00:22:43.780
