00:42:04.420 --> 00:42:12.519
the last hundred or so years, this whole equatorial
forest belt, incredibly wide, right across

00:42:12.519 --> 00:42:23.131
Africa. And just in 80 years of technology,
chainsaws, demand for African hardwoods, these

00:42:23.131 --> 00:42:29.700
areas have been very, very much fragmented.
That whole central area completely gone, fragments

00:42:29.700 --> 00:42:34.589
in the far West of Africa. And that's what
we're all about now is doing everything we

00:42:34.589 --> 00:42:38.349
can do to preserve chimps and chimp habitat.

00:42:38.349 --> 00:42:45.200
During the 90s, I shot this video of Jane.
